headline: Nvidia earnings, Trump's State of the Union: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch next week, starting Monday, Feb. 23. President Trump will deliver his State of the Union address on Tuesday, Feb. 24. It'll be a big week for earnings, with names like Nvidia (NVDA), Salesforce (CRM), Paramount (PSKY), CoreWeave (CRWV), and Dell (DELL) on deck. Federal Reserve commentary is on deck as well, with remarks from names like Fed Governor Lisa Cook and Fed Governor Christopher Waller. The Producer Price Index (PPI) will be out on Friday, with economists expecting headline PPI to cool from the previous month. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
